{"doc":{"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"margin-top","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-top","locale":"en-US","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS\">CSS</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Reference\">CSS Reference</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Box_Model\">CSS Box Model</a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Guides</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Box_Model/Introduction_to_the_CSS_box_model\">Introduction to the CSS basic box model</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Box_Model/Mastering_margin_collapsing\">Mastering margin collapsing</a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/height\"><code>height</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-bottom\"><code>margin-bottom</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-left\"><code>margin-left</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-right\"><code>margin-right</code></a></li><li><em><code>margin-top</code></em></li><li><svg class=\"icon experimental\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" role=\"img\">\n    <title>This is an experimental API that should not be used in production code.</title>\n    <path d=\"M90.72 82.34c4.4 7 1.29 12.66-7 12.66H16.25C8 95 4.88 89.31 9.28 82.34l29.47-46.46V12.5H35A3.75 3.75 0 0135 5h30a3.75 3.75 0 010 7.5h-3.75v23.38zM45.08 39.86L29.14 65h41.72L54.92 39.86l-1.17-1.81V12.5h-7.5v25.55z\"></path>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-trim\"><code>margin-trim</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin\"><code>margin</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/max-height\"><code>max-height</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/max-width\"><code>max-width</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/min-height\"><code>min-height</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/min-width\"><code>min-width</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/overscroll-behavior-block\"><code>overscroll-behavior-block</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/overscroll-behavior-inline\"><code>overscroll-behavior-inline</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/overscroll-behavior-x\"><code>overscroll-behavior-x</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/overscroll-behavior-y\"><code>overscroll-behavior-y</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/overscroll-behavior\"><code>overscroll-behavior</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-bottom\"><code>padding-bottom</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-left\"><code>padding-left</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-right\"><code>padding-right</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-top\"><code>padding-top</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding\"><code>padding</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/visibility\"><code>visibility</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/width\"><code>width</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div></div>\n\n<p>The <strong><code>margin-top</code></strong> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS\">CSS</a> property sets the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Box_Model/Introduction_to_the_CSS_box_model\">margin area</a> on the top of an element. A positive value places it farther from its neighbors, while a negative value places it closer.</p>\n\n<div><iframe class=\"interactive\" width=\"100%\" height=\"250\" src=\"https://interactive-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/pages/css/margin-top.html\" title=\"MDN Web Docs Interactive Example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>\n\n<p class=\"hidden\">The source for this interactive example is stored in a GitHub repository. If you'd like to contribute to the interactive examples project, please clone <a href=\"https://github.com/mdn/interactive-examples\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">https://github.com/mdn/interactive-examples</a> and send us a pull request.</p></div>\n\n\n\n<p>This property has no effect on <em>non-<a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Replaced_element\">replaced</a></em> inline elements, such as <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/span\"><code>&lt;span&gt;</code></a> or <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/code\"><code>&lt;code&gt;</code></a>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"brush:css no-line-numbers notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">/* &lt;length&gt; values */</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">margin-top</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 10px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">/* An absolute length */</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">margin-top</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 1em<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>   <span class=\"token comment\">/* relative to the text size */</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">margin-top</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 5%<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">/* relative to the nearest block container's width */</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* Keyword values */</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">margin-top</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> auto<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* Global values */</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">margin-top</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> inherit<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">margin-top</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> initial<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">margin-top</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> unset<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The <code>margin-top</code> property is specified as the keyword <code>auto</code>, or a <code>&lt;length&gt;</code>, or a <code>&lt;percentage&gt;</code>. Its value can be positive, zero, or negative.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Values","title":"Values","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length\"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a></dt>\n <dd>The size of the margin as a fixed value.</dd>\n <dt><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/percentage\"><code>&lt;percentage&gt;</code></a></dt>\n <dd>The size of the margin as a percentage, relative to the <em>width</em> of the containing block.</dd>\n <dt><code>auto</code></dt>\n <dd>The browser selects a suitable value to use. See <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin\"><code>margin</code></a>.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Formal_definition","title":"Formal definition","isH3":false,"content":"<p><table class=\"properties\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/initial_value\">Initial value</a></th><td><code>0</code></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Applies to</th><td>all elements, except elements with table <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/display\"><code>display</code></a> types other than <code>table-caption</code>, <code>table</code> and <code>inline-table</code>. It also applies to <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/::first-letter\"><code>::first-letter</code></a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/::first-line\"><code>::first-line</code></a>.</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/inheritance\">Inherited</a></th><td>no</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Percentages</th><td>refer to the width of the containing block</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/computed_value\">Computed value</a></th><td>the percentage as specified or the absolute length</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Animation type</th><td>a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length#interpolation\" title=\"Values of the <length> CSS data type are interpolated as real, floating-point numbers.\">length</a></td></tr></tbody></table></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Formal_syntax","title":"Formal syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"notranslate\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length\" title=\"Possible values: a number followed by'em', 'ex', 'ch', 'rem', 'px', 'cm', 'mm', 'in', 'vh', 'vw', 'vmin', 'vmax', 'pt', 'pc' or 'px', like 3px, 1.5cm, -0.5em or 0\">&lt;length&gt;</a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/percentage\" title=\"\">&lt;percentage&gt;</a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> auto</pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Setting_positive_and_negative_top_margins","title":"Setting positive and negative top margins","isH3":true,"content":"<pre class=\"brush:css; notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token selector\">.content</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token property\">margin-top</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>   5%<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token selector\">.sidebox</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token property\">margin-top</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 10px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token selector\">.logo</span>    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token property\">margin-top</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> -5px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token selector\">#footer</span>  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token property\">margin-top</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>  1em<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Specifications","title":"Specifications","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <thead>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Specification</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Comment</th>\n  </tr>\n </thead>\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://drafts.csswg.org/css-box-3/#propdef-margin-top\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">CSS Basic Box Model<br><small lang=\"en-US\">The definition of 'margin-top' in that specification.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-cr\">Candidate Recommendation</span></td>\n   <td>No significant change</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/box.html#margin-properties\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">CSS Level&nbsp;2 (Revision&nbsp;1)<br><small lang=\"en-US\">The definition of 'margin-top' in that specification.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-rec\">Recommendation</span></td>\n   <td>Removes its effect on inline elements.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/CSS1/#margin-top\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">CSS Level&nbsp;1<br><small lang=\"en-US\">The definition of 'margin-top' in that specification.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-rec\">Recommendation</span></td>\n   <td>Initial definition</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"Browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"css.properties.margin-top","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-top/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"See_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-right\"><code>margin-right</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-bottom\"><code>margin-bottom</code></a>, and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-left\"><code>margin-left</code></a> and the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin\"><code>margin</code></a> shorthand</li>\n <li>The mapped logical properties: <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-block-start\"><code>margin-block-start</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-block-end\"><code>margin-block-end</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-inline-start\"><code>margin-inline-start</code></a>, and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-inline-end\"><code>margin-inline-end</code></a> and the shorthands <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-block\"><code>margin-block</code></a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin-inline\"><code>margin-inline</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"Syntax"},{"text":"Formal definition","id":"Formal_definition"},{"text":"Formal syntax","id":"Formal_syntax"},{"text":"Examples","id":"Examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"Specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"Browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"See_also"}],"summary":"The margin-top CSS property sets the margin area on the top of an element. A positive value places it farther from its neighbors, while a negative value places it closer.","popularity":0.0109,"modified":"2021-03-15T17:55:56.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"margin-top","url":"/ca/docs/Web/CSS/margin-top","locale":"ca"},{"title":"margin-top","url":"/de/docs/Web/CSS/margin-top","locale":"de"},{"title":"margin-top","url":"/fr/docs/Web/CSS/margin-top","locale":"fr"},{"title":"margin-top","url":"/ja/docs/Web/CSS/margin-top","locale":"ja"},{"title":"margin-top","url":"/ko/docs/Web/CSS/margin-top","locale":"ko"},{"title":"margin-top","url":"/pt-BR/docs/Web/CSS/margin-top","locale":"pt-BR"},{"title":"margin-top","url":"/ru/docs/Web/CSS/margin-to